FBIS4-43467 "drweu117_b_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-117 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 BENELUX Defense Minister Rules Out Intervention in Rwanda Defense Minister Rules Out Intervention in Rwanda LD1606165294 Brussels La Une Radio Network in French 1600 GMT 16 Jun 94 LD1606165294 Brussels La Une Radio Network French BFN [Excerpt] [passage omitted] [Announcer] Belgian Defense Minister Leo Delcroix is in favor of logistical aid only: [Begin recording] [Delcroix] I do not think it will be a good thing for Belgium to participate actively in the field and on Rwandan territory after the events of the last few months. However, we would like to examine the possibility of logistical aid. [Unidentified correspondent] Does Leo Delcroix exclude an intervention that would take place outside the UN framework? [Delcroix] I do not know about outside the UN framework, but certainly in full agreement with the United Nations. [end recording] [passage omitted]
